19:42.729 --> 19:45.698
or improve a place like this had reason
to make the effort.

19:45.732 --> 19:48.166
The color brought
commerce here,

19:48.201 --> 19:52.001
and such order
as has been attained.

19:52.038 --> 19:53.903
Yes, sir.

19:53.940 --> 19:56.431
Do you want to help
Liberia, Odell?

19:56.476 --> 19:58.467
I want
to help myself.

19:58.512 --> 20:00.980
If Liberia is where
my chance is,

20:01.014 --> 20:03.482
it's all right
with me.

20:03.517 --> 20:05.348
Gold is
your chance.

20:05.385 --> 20:07.979
- Thank you, sir.
- Gold is every man's opportunity.

20:08.021 --> 20:10.080
Why do I make
that argument?

20:10.123 --> 20:13.854
Because every
defect in a man

20:13.894 --> 20:16.124
and in others'
way of taking him,

20:16.162 --> 20:18.687
our agreement
that gold has value

20:18.732 --> 20:21.963
gives us power
to rise above.

20:22.002 --> 20:23.663
Fond as you are
of my mother,

20:23.703 --> 20:25.398
without that gold
I showed you,

20:25.438 --> 20:27.372
I don't expect we'd
be out here talking.

20:27.407 --> 20:29.204
That is correct.

20:29.242 --> 20:32.405
And, for your effrontery at our meal
a moment ago...

20:34.047 --> 20:37.744
I'd have seen you shot or hanged
without a second thought.

20:39.352 --> 20:42.014
The value
I gave the gold

20:42.055 --> 20:44.114
restrained me,
you see...

20:45.559 --> 20:48.392
your utility
in connection to it.

20:48.428 --> 20:51.488
And because of my gold,
those at the other tables

20:51.531 --> 20:53.590
deferred
to my restraint.

20:55.335 --> 20:57.565
Gold confers power.

20:57.604 --> 21:00.300
Power comes to any man
who has the color.

21:00.407 --> 21:02.398
Even if
he's black?

21:04.911 --> 21:07.243
That is our
species' hope:

21:07.280 --> 21:10.408
that uniformly agreeing
on its value,

21:10.450 --> 21:13.248
we organize to seek
the color.

21:18.658 --> 21:20.649
Just before
you and I met, Odell,

21:20.694 --> 21:24.653
the camp's sheriff
released me from a jail cell.

21:24.698 --> 21:29.567
- That's hard for me to feature.
- I hate these places, Odell,

21:29.603 --> 21:31.935
because the truth
that I know,

21:31.972 --> 21:34.202
the promise
that I bring,

21:34.240 --> 21:37.403
the necessities I'm prepared to accept
make me outcast.

21:45.986 --> 21:47.977
Isn't that foolish?

21:49.756 --> 21:51.815
Isn't that foolishness?

21:54.227 --> 21:56.923
An old man
disabused long ago

21:56.963 --> 21:59.989
of certain yearnings
and hopes

22:00.100 --> 22:02.967
as to how he would be held
by his fellows,

22:03.002 --> 22:05.905
and yet I weep.

22:09.676 --> 22:11.644
Anyway, sir,

22:11.678 --> 22:13.509
you want to send
someone back with me?

22:13.546 --> 22:15.377
Yes, I do.

22:16.583 --> 22:18.483
Yes, I do, son.

22:18.518 --> 22:21.646
I want to send you
to help your people...

22:23.990 --> 22:26.857
and take this place down
like Gomorrah.

22:31.164 --> 22:32.995
All being affected,

22:33.033 --> 22:36.400
we might consider
some facts as a group.

22:36.436 --> 22:39.735
I arrested Hearst, acting in the name
of the camp.

22:39.773 --> 22:42.298
Without the camp's
previous fucking say-so.

22:42.342 --> 22:44.503
Do you propose that?

22:44.544 --> 22:47.206
Getting a say-so
before I do my duty?

22:50.750 --> 22:54.242
Might be a good open...
showing Hearst it's off of him.

22:54.287 --> 22:56.721
Bullock's tin won't
placate Hearst.

22:56.756 --> 22:58.951
Give it the fuck
back to him.

23:01.628 --> 23:03.493
Add to your statement
or shut the fuck up.

23:03.530 --> 23:05.623
I'm done.

23:05.665 --> 23:08.463
Shall I, as Mayor,
initiate proceedings

23:08.501 --> 23:10.628
by giving
my own opinions,

23:10.670 --> 23:13.298
however titular

23:13.339 --> 23:15.739
and insubstantial

23:15.775 --> 23:18.573
and merely honorific
the position?

23:19.946 --> 23:22.676
Which argues
against my doing so.

23:23.683 --> 23:25.981
How is Hearst
likely to answer?

23:26.019 --> 23:28.749
Ought steps to be taken
in preemption?

23:28.788 --> 23:31.723
My instinct's
to act alone,

23:31.758 --> 23:33.817
chart the course
for fucking carnage.

23:33.860 --> 23:36.192
That this
would be general

23:36.229 --> 23:38.697
among 'em whose parents were so dim
as to bring them...

23:38.732 --> 23:42.725
the fucking innocence is
what gives me fucking pause.

23:44.571 --> 23:47.665
I invite the suggestions
of others

23:47.707 --> 23:50.608
against my instinct
to send for the guns.

23:56.616 --> 23:59.813
As I've expressed
to the sheriff

23:59.919 --> 24:02.620
and Mr. Star,

24:02.655 --> 24:04.987
and siding
with your instincts,

24:05.024 --> 24:08.653
to protect the innocents,
I'd send them from the camp.

24:08.695 --> 24:11.994
Then fall on Hearst
and his in their lair

24:12.031 --> 24:15.797
before they fall
on us in ours.

24:22.575 --> 24:25.874
As Wild Bill
would have done.

24:52.405 --> 24:55.135
This is
a letter.

24:55.175 --> 24:57.370
Who's the fucking letter to?

24:57.410 --> 25:00.106
What the fuck
is going on?

25:00.213 --> 25:02.704
- Last of those Cornishmen murdered.
- Pasco.

25:02.739 --> 25:05.344
- His family.
- Read the letter.

25:09.622 --> 25:13.524
"It becomes my painful duty
to inform you that Pasco Carwen

25:13.560 --> 25:16.654
- was killed earlier this week."
- Stop poking your head out.

25:16.696 --> 25:19.665
I'm seeing who's using
the cinnamon,

25:19.699 --> 25:22.566
and Harry Manning's
using it plenty.

25:22.602 --> 25:25.469
"...was not mutilated
in any way.

25:25.505 --> 25:28.099
His death seems
to have been instantaneous

25:28.141 --> 25:30.268
as he was stabbed
through the heart.

25:30.310 --> 25:33.507
Pasco's funeral
occurred today

25:33.546 --> 25:36.208
and was attended
by coworkers and friends

25:36.249 --> 25:39.218
who all shared the same
high opinion of him.

25:39.252 --> 25:41.777
Everything was done
by kind hands

25:41.821 --> 25:44.312
that was possible
under the circumstances,

25:44.357 --> 25:47.656
and a Christian burial
was given him.

25:47.694 --> 25:51.186
I was not personally
acquainted with Mr. Carwen,

25:51.231 --> 25:54.667
save for one encounter
where he demonstrated grief

25:54.701 --> 25:57.568
and deep compassion
at the passing of a friend.

25:57.604 --> 26:01.062
I knew him by reputation
as an earnest worker

26:01.174 --> 26:05.634
and a diligent believer
in right and wrong.

26:05.669 --> 26:08.240
His memory I am sure
will always be

26:08.281 --> 26:10.749
with those
who knew and loved him,

26:10.783 --> 26:14.549
among whose number
I imagine you as first.

26:14.587 --> 26:18.387
A letter from you
which I found in his tent

26:18.424 --> 26:22.087
causes me to convey
this sad intelligence to you.

26:22.128 --> 26:25.825
Sincerely yours,
Seth Bullock."

26:30.069 --> 26:32.367
What shall I do
with this, Mr. Bullock?

26:35.275 --> 26:37.766
What's your fucking
paper for?

26:37.810 --> 26:39.835
You fucking publish
as witness,

26:39.879 --> 26:42.609
for Hearst
and others to read.

26:45.752 --> 26:48.118
That's a very nice
fucking letter.

27:00.133 --> 27:02.226
Mr. Blazanov,

27:02.268 --> 27:05.396
had you much traffic tonight
on your apparatus?

27:05.438 --> 27:08.066
Some traffic, yes.

27:08.107 --> 27:11.440
I hope your important meeting
had a good result.

27:11.477 --> 27:13.570
As free men

27:13.613 --> 27:15.672
facing important
challenges,

27:15.715 --> 27:18.809
we choose
to be optimistic.

27:21.154 --> 27:23.088
Sir, I ask you

27:23.122 --> 27:25.613
take me
to Mr. Swearengen's place.

27:25.658 --> 27:28.684
Well, I... I will,
of course, Mr. Blazanov,

27:28.728 --> 27:31.663
though no activity
you may contemplate,

27:31.698 --> 27:35.099
for example, the making of friends
with his female employees,

27:35.134 --> 27:37.796
requires Mr. Swearengen's
personal approval.

27:37.837 --> 27:41.671
I wish to see him
for another purpose.

27:43.776 --> 27:46.210
All right.

27:47.747 --> 27:49.840
Shall we go now?

27:49.882 --> 27:51.816
Certainly.

27:57.590 --> 27:59.581
Mmm.

28:03.396 --> 28:04.761
Come on.

28:08.167 --> 28:09.896
Lovely letter,
wasn't it?

28:09.936 --> 28:11.801
Didn't you...

28:11.838 --> 28:14.170
come back sick from one
of them meetings?

28:14.207 --> 28:16.767
Last year,
from the peaches.

28:16.809 --> 28:19.141
Which is why I refrained
this time around.

28:19.178 --> 28:22.045
Far as
the fire wagon,

28:22.081 --> 28:24.049
I gather you felt
as I did,

28:24.083 --> 28:25.846
the moment was wrong
to broach it.

28:25.885 --> 28:27.750
My... my throat

28:27.787 --> 28:30.381
is all
fucking tight.

28:32.358 --> 28:34.826
Where did you lay
your hands on liquor, Harry?

28:34.861 --> 28:37.227
Harry?

28:37.263 --> 28:39.823
Help! Harry?

28:40.900 --> 28:43.198
Harry! Help!

28:43.302 --> 28:45.503
Oh.

28:45.538 --> 28:47.938
Look, Jack.

28:47.974 --> 28:50.499
White lumps on my tongue.

28:50.543 --> 28:52.374
Reel it in,
for God's sake.

28:52.412 --> 28:54.039
I'm so sorry.

28:54.080 --> 28:56.446
It's close, Jack.

28:56.482 --> 28:58.712
It's very close.

28:58.818 --> 29:01.048
I feel it's...
it's at breath.

29:01.087 --> 29:04.079
I hear it whispering
in my ear.

29:04.123 --> 29:06.091
"Forget your name.

29:06.125 --> 29:08.650
We go to black."

29:10.897 --> 29:13.058
The downstairs buffet
is quite passable.

29:17.870 --> 29:19.531
Oh.

29:19.572 --> 29:21.597
As like to kill you
as take passage

29:21.641 --> 29:23.609
with you to Liberia,

29:23.643 --> 29:25.975
his man you meeting
in New York.

29:26.012 --> 29:28.105
If Mr. Hearst
wanted me killed, Mama,

29:28.147 --> 29:30.672
- he could see it done here.
- Don't you ever believe

29:30.716 --> 29:32.581
you know what'd
please that man,

29:32.618 --> 29:34.711
or salt him
to come after you.

29:36.489 --> 29:39.322
And you look a fool
holding that cigar!

29:40.927 --> 29:43.088
I've played one
for smaller stakes.

29:44.163 --> 29:45.960
And the gold
ain't playing.

29:45.998 --> 29:47.625
I ain't trying
to steal nothing.

29:47.667 --> 29:48.964
I'll work my way
up the hog.

29:49.001 --> 29:51.799
And ain't you sent me out there
so I can turn out a man?

29:51.838 --> 29:55.740
I sent you so the hell that was coming
here for niggers wouldn't burn you up.

29:55.775 --> 29:57.640
There's plenty
of fire in Liberia.

29:57.677 --> 30:00.475
I can't undo
what I done, Odell,

30:00.513 --> 30:02.481
any more than you can,
searching out hurt.

30:02.515 --> 30:04.506
I ain't searching
no hurt out.

30:04.550 --> 30:07.815
We all get our portion.
We don't need to draw it to us.

30:07.854 --> 30:10.755
You hear me, Mama?
I ain't searching no goddamn hurt out.

30:10.790 --> 30:13.315
I done told you to mind
who you talking to.

30:13.359 --> 30:16.988
All right, Mama.
No bad language.

30:17.029 --> 30:20.430
If you'd kept me
to raise me, maybe I'd know.

30:27.940 --> 30:30.807
He got $742 for you,

30:30.843 --> 30:32.811
the little nigger
at the livery.

30:32.845 --> 30:35.211
And this brooch here too,
you can take.

30:35.248 --> 30:37.239
I can't find it.

30:37.283 --> 30:39.274
I can't
find it.

30:39.318 --> 30:41.309
Lord Jesus,
forgive me!

30:42.355 --> 30:44.823
When I read you had
stayed in the Comstock,

30:44.857 --> 30:47.052
I tried to come
here quick,

30:47.093 --> 30:49.789
be gone before he
sent for you to come.

30:49.829 --> 30:52.229
I ain't come here
to hurt you.

30:52.265 --> 30:55.063
I never said
you come to do me hurt.

30:55.101 --> 30:58.537
So's you wouldn't
have to see me.

30:58.638 --> 31:01.766
I prayed to see you
every day you was gone.

31:01.801 --> 31:05.404
My God, Odell,
what's wrong with you?

31:05.444 --> 31:08.242
No joy to seeing
my boy!

31:11.017 --> 31:14.817
- I'm sorry, son.
- Hush, Mama. Hush. Hush.

31:14.854 --> 31:17.914
Oh, do what you
think you got to.

31:17.957 --> 31:20.790
I couldn't find
the right.

31:20.826 --> 31:23.659
Hush now, Mama.
Hush.

31:23.696 --> 31:25.323
Oh!

31:25.364 --> 31:27.730
I got you now.

31:27.767 --> 31:30.235
"Bricks."
You see there?

31:30.269 --> 31:32.066
Yes, I see.

31:32.104 --> 31:35.733
"Bricks.
25 bricks. Stop.

31:35.775 --> 31:38.073
Addition to initial
order. Stop.

31:38.110 --> 31:40.271
First means
of delivery. Stop."

31:40.313 --> 31:42.781
And, Blazanov?

31:42.815 --> 31:44.806
Do you believe,
Mr. Swearengen,

31:44.850 --> 31:48.251
Mr. Hearst orders
more bricks?

31:48.287 --> 31:49.914
No.

31:49.956 --> 31:51.856
What do
you believe?

31:52.792 --> 31:55.852
I believe he orders
more humans.

31:55.895 --> 31:58.921
- Reinforcements.
- To do harm!

31:59.031 --> 32:01.192
As we saw
on our walk.

32:01.234 --> 32:04.761
Leave to die in a country
strange to them,

32:04.804 --> 32:07.967
men apart
from their families,

32:08.007 --> 32:10.737
working to give
them support.

32:12.712 --> 32:16.307
Fuck confidentiality
of communications.

32:16.349 --> 32:19.910
- Why not fuck a woman instead?
- I hope so eventually.

32:19.952 --> 32:22.182
Now I deliver
under seal

32:22.221 --> 32:24.416
his message
to Mr. Hearst.

32:24.457 --> 32:27.392
I'll dispose
of this, Blazanov.

32:35.101 --> 32:37.433
How are you occupying
yourself, Richardson?

32:37.470 --> 32:40.496
I'm praying
the meeting went well.

32:40.539 --> 32:42.598
Very touching.

32:42.642 --> 32:45.907
Now clear your mind
of the meeting

32:45.945 --> 32:49.005
and account for
the Negro with Hearst.

32:50.016 --> 32:51.813
They're both
in her room.

32:54.520 --> 32:56.647
Despite your best efforts,
Richardson,

32:56.689 --> 32:58.953
an answer
of some ambiguity.

33:01.027 --> 33:02.790
Is she with them?

33:02.828 --> 33:05.456
- One.
- One what?

33:05.498 --> 33:07.489
Of them.
Is with her.

33:07.533 --> 33:10.024
- Who?
- Aunt Lou.

33:10.069 --> 33:12.765
- Who is with Aunt Lou?
- Her son.

33:14.206 --> 33:15.867
And where is Hearst?

33:15.908 --> 33:18.206
His room.

33:19.478 --> 33:21.708
Then I will
retire to mine.

33:21.747 --> 33:23.738
Well, how was
the meeting?

33:28.888 --> 33:32.255
I imagine the pool
that spawned you.

33:32.291 --> 33:34.452
I am filling it
with rocks.

33:34.493 --> 33:37.951
I am holding shut
your gills

33:37.997 --> 33:40.022
to prevent you
from taking in air.

33:44.470 --> 33:47.234
I suppose the meeting
went quite well.

33:55.614 --> 33:58.549
I itch.

33:58.651 --> 34:00.050
- Dust.
- No matter how much

34:00.086 --> 34:03.852
regularity of cleaning or consideration
for the children,

34:03.889 --> 34:05.857
a place like this
is filled with dust.

34:10.862 --> 34:12.728
He's dead.

34:12.764 --> 34:14.527
Chesterton is
with us still,

34:14.567 --> 34:17.434
though to bring him in the evening chill
would be imprudent.

34:17.469 --> 34:19.802
We'll bring him
tomorrow

34:19.839 --> 34:22.569
when this room
is less cold.

34:22.608 --> 34:25.907
After the children have gone and before
you bring him,

34:25.945 --> 34:27.879
I will give the place
a good dust.

34:27.913 --> 34:29.608
Then the carpentry
will begin.

34:29.648 --> 34:31.547
You've engaged
the carpenters?

34:31.583 --> 34:33.779
Yes.

34:33.819 --> 34:36.014
He is close to the end,
isn't he?

34:36.054 --> 34:38.784
Yes, Bellegarde!

34:38.824 --> 34:40.724
For Christ's sake!

35:02.348 --> 35:04.578
Haunted.

35:04.617 --> 35:07.484
Drafts from all over.

35:07.520 --> 35:09.750
From the walls,
from the side,

35:09.789 --> 35:12.189
swooping down
from the ceiling.

35:12.224 --> 35:15.318
I will dust anyway
for Chesterton,

35:15.361 --> 35:20.128
even though after,
the carpenters come.

35:20.166 --> 35:22.066
Uh, the attitude
on people leaving

35:22.101 --> 35:25.298
definitely stepped forward
from the attitude they wore coming in.

35:25.337 --> 35:27.601
I mean, no one's trying
to quarrel about that.

35:27.640 --> 35:30.871
Then what's your quarrel?

35:30.910 --> 35:33.879
I'm asking
what was decided.

35:35.114 --> 35:38.345
They're publishing
the letter as witness.

35:38.384 --> 35:41.751
- Witness?
- A witness in the sense that...

35:41.787 --> 35:45.917
Witness the letter...
its content.

35:45.958 --> 35:48.654
Yeah, the letter's
contents is witness

35:48.694 --> 35:50.321
that...

35:50.362 --> 35:53.229
Bullock wrote
a nice fucking letter.

35:54.800 --> 35:58.258
And it proves...

35:58.370 --> 36:00.497
that that's the sort
we are here,

36:00.539 --> 36:03.440
the caring sort that
would write a letter of that ilk.

36:03.476 --> 36:07.105
Furthermore, we don't
give a fuck who knows it,

36:07.146 --> 36:09.205
George fucking Hearst
included.

36:09.248 --> 36:10.909
Fucking Hearst
especially.

36:11.984 --> 36:13.542
Is the witness?

36:13.586 --> 36:16.146
Better late than
fucking never, Johnny.

36:19.492 --> 36:23.189
Hey! Little Miss
Fucking Cinnamon.

36:56.362 --> 36:59.354
I wanna be good.

37:00.633 --> 37:03.227
I wanna be good.

37:18.517 --> 37:20.610
Good evening.

37:24.056 --> 37:25.614
Good evening.

37:31.730 --> 37:33.527
For being gone, I...

37:33.566 --> 37:35.557
I notice
I'm frequently back.

37:37.503 --> 37:40.063
I come to kiss her
good night.

37:40.105 --> 37:43.040
I tried to persuade her
you'd done so last night.

37:43.075 --> 37:44.633
My beard always
wakes her.

37:44.677 --> 37:47.737
She said so,
refuting me.

37:52.851 --> 37:54.819
The thing I did

37:54.853 --> 37:56.718
that made you leave
last night,

37:56.755 --> 38:01.021
the thing I was coming home
to do again...

38:02.161 --> 38:04.925
I pray now
to forego forever.

38:04.964 --> 38:08.092
Not having me in this house is gonna
improve your odds.

38:08.133 --> 38:11.830
I started using spirits
at 17, Ellsworth,

38:11.870 --> 38:14.100
with no premonition
we'd marry.

38:14.139 --> 38:16.903
Well, my feeling's
that being vessel

38:16.942 --> 38:20.503
of purposes not your own,
your eye was out for relief.

38:20.546 --> 38:22.514
But glimpsing since

38:22.548 --> 38:25.676
how being your own vessel
is preferable,

38:25.718 --> 38:28.778
let the pressure
come off

38:28.821 --> 38:31.051
and you're liable
to do all right.

38:32.725 --> 38:35.956
You are no pressure.

38:35.995 --> 38:38.293
My...

38:38.330 --> 38:40.855
friendly hands'll

38:40.899 --> 38:43.299
always be out
to both of you.

38:50.042 --> 38:53.808
May I interrupt
her sleep with this beard?

38:55.781 --> 38:58.750
She'd be so glad
if you did.

39:15.300 --> 39:19.066
- Yes?
- Cheyenne and Black Hills Telegraph.

39:19.104 --> 39:21.072
Yes, all right.

39:33.752 --> 39:36.243
- Evening.
- Telegram for Mr. Hearst.

39:36.288 --> 39:38.256
Ah, thank you.

39:38.290 --> 39:41.521
I wonder if you might remain
just a moment while I read it,

39:41.560 --> 39:43.687
on the chance
I'll want to answer.

39:43.729 --> 39:45.720
Of course.

39:47.166 --> 39:50.101
